description: Minority religious leaders in Bangladesh have appealed to interim government chief adviser Muhammad Yunus to consider the bail plea of Hindu monk Chinmoy Krishna Das, facing sedition charges.  A bail hearing is rescheduled for January 2nd.  Two individuals were remanded in Chittagong concerning the death of Saiful Islam Alif, who died in clashes following the denial of Das's bail.
title: Obtaining bail is a right, monk's plea must be heard, religious heads tell Yunus

description: The Supreme Court is examining a PIL alleging retaliatory actions against Internal Complaints Committee (ICC) members in private companies who rule against senior management in sexual harassment cases. The petitioners argue that ICC members need protection and job security to ensure fair decisions without fear of reprisal, similar to the protections afforded to judges.
title: PIL flags job threat to private companies' ICC members

description: External Affairs Minister S. Jaishankar expressed confidence that the incoming Trump administration will continue to support the Quad, crediting Trump for its resurgence.  Jaishankar highlighted the Quad's upgrades during Trump's first term and the recent disengagement with China in eastern Ladakh, while acknowledging the remaining de-escalation challenges.
title: EAM hopes new Trump govt will back Quad, credits earlier admin for upgrade

description: The Supreme Court criticized the Enforcement Directorate's overnight interrogation and 4 a.m. arrest of ex-IAS officer Anil Tuteja in the Chhattisgarh liquor scam as "terrible" and "disturbing." While upholding the arrest, the Court permitted Tuteja to seek bail.  The ED, facing scrutiny for its methods, issued an internal circular curbing late-night interrogations following the incident.
title: ED quizzing ex-official whole night in liquor case 'terrible': SC

description: Finance Minister Nirmala Sitharaman asserted that the slower second-quarter growth doesn't signal a systemic slowdown, attributing it to reduced public spending during the election season.  She anticipates a rebound in the third quarter and maintains India's position as the fastest-growing major economy for the coming years, despite global economic challenges and climate change impacts.
title: 5.4% GDP growth doesn't indicate systemic slowdown: FM Sitharaman

description: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) maintained its policy rate at 6.5% but lowered the economic growth forecast for 2024-25 to 6.6% from 7.2%. A CRR cut to 4% will release ₹1.6 lakh crore for banks. The RBI acknowledged a recent economic slowdown but anticipates a recovery driven by festive demand and improved agricultural output.
title: RBI cuts CRR 50 bps, trims FY25 GDP forecast to 6.6%

description: Kansas City Chiefs star Travis Kelce is preparing a grand proposal for Taylor Swift. He is planning to spend $12 million on an engagement ring. Kelce aims to create an unforgettable experience. He is scouting locations and wants the proposal to inspire a Swift song. The couple has spent holidays together.
title: Travis Kelce planning $12 million engagement ring for Taylor Swift

description: A wad of cash was discovered on Congress MP Abhishek Manu Singhvi's Rajya Sabha seat, prompting an inquiry.  Singhvi denied ownership and called for an investigation into the security lapse, while BJP members demanded a probe into the incident.
title: Dhankhar says cash found on Singhvi's Rajya Sabha seat, sparks row

description: Himachal Pradesh Governor Shiv Pratap Shukla boycotted an event commemorating Dr. B.R. Ambedkar's death anniversary due to perceived disrespect in the invitation. Shukla stated he wasn't contacted personally by officials and the invitation listed the Chief Minister as the chief guest, prompting him to pay tribute at Raj Bhawan instead.
title: Irked by 'simple' invite, Himachal guv skips civic body Ambedkar event

description: An Armyman's wife died in Meerut after a hospital lift malfunctioned and crashed following her delivery.  The woman suffered fatal head and neck injuries.  The hospital has been sealed and its license revoked. Police have filed a culpable homicide case against the hospital owner, doctor, and staff.
title: After giving birth, woman dies as hospital lift belt snaps

description: Uttarakhand is set to implement a green cess on out-of-state vehicles starting next month.  The cess, ranging from ₹20 to ₹80, will be collected via FASTag, utilizing automatic number-plate recognition.  Two-wheelers, CNG, and electric vehicles are exempt, along with government and emergency vehicles.  Tenders for the required equipment are currently open, closing on December 11.
title: Cars entering Uttarakhand to pay green cess; EVs, bikes exempted

description: The Supreme Court criticized the Allahabad High Court's practice of granting stays and delaying hearings, highlighting a child custody case where a stay lasted five years. A woman, separated from her husband since 2018, sought custody of her son.
title: SC frowns at 'stay and forget orders' in high courts

description: Horoscope Today: Read daily horoscope predictions for December 7, 2024. Know all about the astrological events and influences that will be affecting each of the 12 zodiac signs.  Our astrologer has analyzed the movements of the planets and the alignment of the stars to bring you the most accurate and up-to-date horoscope predictions for the day ahead. Get ready to discover what the stars have in store for you today.
title: Horoscope : Read your today's astrological predictions

description: A 17-year-old student fatally shot his school principal, Surendra Kumar Saxena, in Chhatarpur district, Madhya Pradesh.  The student shot Saxena in the school washroom after being warned about his behavior. He then fled on the principal's scooter but was apprehended near the Uttar Pradesh border, still possessing the pistol. Police are investigating how the student obtained the firearm.
title: Class 12 student shoots principal in washroom

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi highlighted the Northeast's development progress, emphasizing a shift from vote-centric politics to infrastructure investment, social initiatives, and peace-building.  Reduced violence, historic peace agreements, and over Rs 5 lakh crore investment in the past decade showcase the region's growing importance in India's future, with improved connectivity and a focus on its cultural and economic strengths.
title: Northeast ignored for years, our government reversed trend: PM Modi

description: Mitchell Starc's six-wicket haul propelled Australia to a dominant position on Day 1 of the Pink-ball Test against India.  Australia bowled India out for 180, with Starc leading the attack.  Despite a late fightback from India, Australia finished the day strongly at 86/1, thanks to resilient batting from Labuschagne and McSweeney.
title: Starc makes honest Jaiswal admission, says...

description: The Madhya Pradesh government's unemployment allowance scheme, CM Yuva Sambal Yojana, faces arrears of Rs 300-350 crore, with payments delayed since March 2024. Lakhs of unemployed youth await disbursement, while the finance department assures prompt settlement.
title: 8-month delay in paying unemployment dole under CM Yuva Sambal Yojana

description: India advises its citizens to avoid all travel to Syria due to escalating violence and recommends immediate departure for those currently there.  Approximately 90 Indians, including 14 UN workers, are in Syria. The Indian Embassy is in contact with them, ensuring their safety amidst renewed rebel attacks threatening President Assad's control.
title: MEA issues travel advisory amid escalating violence in Syria

description: Allu Arjun expressed grief over the death of a woman during a stampede at the Hyderabad premiere of Pushpa 2. He offered condolences, promised personal support to the family, and announced a ₹25 lakh donation.  Police are investigating the theatre management, Allu Arjun, and his security team.
title: Allu Arjun pledges Rs 25L to kin of woman who died during 'Pushpa 2' screening

description: El Salvador's Bitcoin investment, exceeding $600 million, has seen remarkable gains since its initial investment.  Bitcoin's surge past $100,000, fueled by Trump's election and pro-crypto SEC chair appointment, further boosted El Salvador's holdings.  Despite warnings, the country continues its Bitcoin embrace, aiming to empower its unbanked population.
title: El Salvador president shares country's Bitcoin success; gets reply from Musk

description: Actor Vijay criticised both the BJP-led central government and the DMK-led Tamil Nadu government.
title: Vijay continues his tirade against NDA and DMK govts, suggests a ‘simple solution’
113 new schools and Rithala-Kundli metro corridor approved by Cabinet

description: Rajender Meghwar, hailing from Badin, Sindh, has etched his name in history as the first Hindu officer in Pakistan's Police Service (PSP). Successfully clearing the CSS exam, he now serves as Assistant Superintendent of Police (ASP) in Faisalabad.
title: Meet Rajender Meghwar, Pakistan police's first Hindu officer

description: Eknath Shinde, after being sworn in as Maharashtra's deputy chief minister, has requested the home ministry portfolio.  Shiv Sena leader Bharat Gogavale stated that discussions are ongoing, and a cabinet expansion is expected between December 11 and 16.  The BJP secured a significant victory in the state elections, winning 132 seats.
title: Shinde has demanded home ministry, claims Sena MLA amid portfolio talks

description: The Milwaukee Bucks and Boston Celtics face off tonight at TD Garden.  A potential season debut for Khris Middleton adds intrigue, while stars Giannis Antetokounmpo and Jayson Tatum lead their respective teams.  Injury concerns surround key players on both sides. Tune in at 7:30 pm ET on ESPN, NBC Sports Boston, or FanDuel Sports Network - Wisconsin.
title: Milwaukee Bucks vs Boston Celtics (12/6): Injury report, start time & more

description: Travis Kelce is planning an "extra special" 35th birthday celebration for his girlfriend, Taylor Swift, on December 13.  He's been shopping for months, selecting gifts from her wish list. Despite his game schedule, Kelce is determined to celebrate both her birthday and Christmas with her.  Their relationship has been a public spectacle, with mutual support at games and concerts.
title: Travis Kelce plans to make beau Taylor Swift's 35th birthday 'extra special'

description: Currency notes were discovered at Congress MP Abhishek Manu Singhvi's Rajya Sabha seat during a routine security check.  This sparked accusations from the BJP and counterclaims from Congress, who called it a diversionary tactic to avoid discussion of the Adani issue.  The BJP demanded a thorough investigation, while Congress objected to Singhvi being named before the probe's conclusion.
title: Currency notes in Rajya Sabha 'diversion tactics', alleges Congress; BJP seeks probe

description: Kansas City Chiefs tight end Travis Kelce publicly acknowledged his struggles connecting with quarterback Patrick Mahomes. Kelce expressed frustration with his own performance and the lack of synergy with Mahomes, impacting his touchdown numbers. Despite this, Kelce defended Mahomes against criticism from his brother, Jason Kelce, demonstrating their underlying friendship.
title: Travis Kelce opens up about his struggles and tension with Patrick Mahomes

description: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) has raised the interest rate ceiling on Foreign Currency Non-Resident (Bank) or FCNR(B) deposits to attract more foreign currency. For deposits maturing in one to less than three years, the new ceiling is the overnight Alternative Reference Rate (ARR) plus 400 basis points, effective until March 2025.
title: Cheer for NRIs! Earn higher interest rates on FCNR(B) deposits till March 31, 2025 - here’s how

description: Adelaide Oval witnessed unexpected floodlight failures during the second India-Australia Test, interrupting play twice. The incident occurred during India's bowling attack, disrupting pacer Harshit Rana's rhythm and triggering humorous reactions on social media. Despite the interruptions, play resumed, with Australia ending Day 1 at 86/1, trailing India by 94 runs after they were bowled out for 180.

description: Virat Kohli's on-field energy and antics were on full display during the first day of the pink-ball Test against Australia. Kohli's praise for Jasprit Bumrah's bowling and his superstitious bail-swapping highlighted the day's play. However, India struggled with the bat, bowled out for 180, with Kohli himself falling for just seven.

description: A Beverly Hills teacher, Joanie Garratt, alleges she was fired for criticizing pro-Trump student behavior and the former president on her private Facebook account. The school district denies firing her, claiming she was a substitute teacher whose assignment ended. The incident followed a pro-Trump rally where students allegedly harassed minority groups, sparking debate about free speech and educator responsibilities.

description: A technical glitch during the second Test displayed Mohammed Siraj bowling a jaw-dropping 181.6 kmph thunderbolt against Australia in the day-night Test.  The actual recorder fastest ball bowled is 161.3 kmph by Shoaib Akhtar.  Australia ended day one at 86 for 1 in reply to India's 180, trailing by 94 runs. Mitchell Starc took 6 wickets for Australia, while Jasprit Bumrah took one for India.

description: Mamta Kulkarni clarified her past relationship with Vicky Goswami, while Salman Khan displayed protective behavior towards MLA Zeeshan Siddique amidst security concerns.  A Honey Singh documentary is set to premiere, and Vivek Oberoi opened up about past underworld threats. description: Indian cricketer Jasprit Bumrah celebrated his 31st birthday amidst a shower of well-wishes, including a charming Instagram post from his wife, Sanjana Ganesan, featuring their son, Angad. description: India has demanded Pakistan take decisive action against Masood Azhar, the Jaish-e-Mohammed chief, following reports of a public speech he gave in Pakistan.  India highlighted Pakistan's denial of Azhar's presence despite his involvement in attacks like the 2019 Pulwama attack and the 2001 Parliament attack.  Azhar, designated a global terrorist, has long-standing ties with Pakistani intelligence.

description: Indian-origin comedian Kabir Singh, known for his appearance on America's Got Talent, passed away at 39.  He was found dead in his sleep on Wednesday, December 5th. The industry now faces scrutiny over its practices and security measures.

description: The Golden State Warriors, potentially with Stephen Curry back, face the Minnesota Timberwolves, who are on a three-game winning streak.  Draymond Green is also probable for the Warriors.  Despite recent dominance by the Timberwolves, the Warriors are favored if Curry plays at his usual level. The game tips off at 10 PM ET on December 6, 2024, at Chase Center.

description: Bill Gates reminisced about his free-range childhood, contrasting it with modern parenting dilemmas. He highlighted the benefits of real-world experiences while acknowledging the challenges of digital-age parenting.  Gates warned against both digital under-parenting and real-world over-parenting, suggesting they contribute to addiction-like behaviors and hinder resilience in young people.

description: During the India-Australia pink ball Test, Virat Kohli, known for his superstitions, swapped the bails hoping to break a stubborn partnership between Aussie batters McSweeney and Labuschagne.  Despite Kohli's attempt, reminiscent of a similar act by Stuart Broad in the Ashes, Australia finished day one at 86/1, trailing India by 94 runs after bowling the visitors out for 180.

description: Eight people were killed and 40 injured when a double-decker bus collided with a tanker on the Agra-Lucknow Expressway in Kannauj district on Friday. The bus, traveling from Lucknow to Delhi, reportedly hit the tanker watering plants along the divider. UP minister Swatantra Dev Singh, present at the scene, aided rescue efforts.

description: Syrian rebels, spearheaded by Hayat Tahrir al-Sham (HTS), are rapidly advancing, capturing Hama and Aleppo, posing a severe threat to the Assad regime. HTS aims to establish itself as an alternative to Assad, exploiting the Syrian military's vulnerabilities. The potential fall of Homs could isolate Assad from his strongholds, raising questions about his regime's survival.

description: Ransomware group Brain Cipher claimed to have breached Deloitte UK, stealing over 1TB of sensitive data.  Deloitte has denied the allegations, stating only a single client's isolated system was impacted and none of the company's systems were compromised.
title: Deloitte responds as hackers claim access to firm's 1TB data

description: Amid the serious discussions, a surprising and surreal narrative emerged: the alleged killer’s unexpected rise as a “thirst trap.” Surveillance images released by law enforcement showed a suspect with striking features, sparking comparisons to actors like Timothée Chalamet and Josh O’Connor—icons of the so-called “Rodent Man” aesthetic. His aggressive knock, combined with a disciplined bowling performance, propelled India to chase down 174 with 170 balls remaining. They will face Bangladesh in the final on Sunday.
title: Suryavanshi stars as India beat SL to make U19 Asia Cup final

description: India suffered a batting collapse on Day 1 of the second Test against Australia, losing nine wickets for 111 runs to be bowled out for 180. Mitchell Starc's career-best 6 for 48 spearheaded the Australian attack. Despite KL Rahul's promising start, he fell for 32, continuing his struggles to convert starts.

Protesters entered the Bangladesh Assistant High Commission in Agartala.

description: Former England captain Kevin Pietersen offered pointed advice to India's struggling batsmen after their first-innings collapse against Australia in the Adelaide pink-ball Test. description: Rishabh Pant's match-winning 89 against Australia at the Gabba in 2021, which secured a historic series victory for India, is still fresh in the minds of cricket fans.

Thompson, 50, was fatally shot while walking to a conference in Midtown Manhattan. Investigators are probing links between the attack and Thompson’s role in the insurance industry, with evidence including engraved shell casings and a suspect using fake IDs.

description: India and Australia's day-night Test at Adelaide Oval had unexpected floodlight issues.  India chose to bat but struggled, scoring 180 runs. Starc took six wickets for Australia. description: Union Agriculture Minister Shivraj Singh Chouhan assured the Rajya Sabha of the government's commitment to procuring all farm produce at MSP. He defended the Modi government's record on MSP, highlighting the 50% profit margin over production costs.  Chouhan emphasized income growth over loan waivers and addressed concerns raised by opposition members regarding MSP and farmer welfare.

description: A Penn State study found that consuming just five mushrooms daily could help protect against diseases like heart disease, cancer, and dementia.  Researchers discovered mushrooms are the richest dietary source of the antioxidants ergothioneine and glutathione.  Porcini mushrooms had the highest levels of these compounds.  Incorporating mushrooms into your diet is easy with various flavorful options for every meal.

description: The Delhi High Court has directed the Central government to clarify its stance on BJP leader Subramanian Swamy's petition questioning Rahul Gandhi's Indian citizenship. Swamy alleges Gandhi declared himself a British citizen to the UK government, violating Indian law.
title: Delhi HC seeks Centre’s response on plea regarding Rahul Gandhi’s citizenship

description: The Indian government has launched PAN 2.0, a program to modernize and digitize PAN and TAN administration.  It will consolidate services, enhance security with QR codes, and identify duplicate PANs.  Holding multiple PANs can result in a penalty.
title: PAN 2.0: Have an extra PAN Card? Surrender now to avoid Rs 10k penalty!

description: In the second pink-ball Test against Australia at Adelaide Oval, young Indian batter Nitish Kumar Reddy top-scored with a gritty 42 in the first innings. Despite India struggling against the pink ball and being bundled out for 180, Reddy's aggressive approach, including an unconventional six, was a highlight.

description: An Indian Army soldier, Jasvinder Singh, died of a cardiac arrest during a search operation in Srinagar, Jammu and Kashmir, following a Tuesday encounter where Lashkar-e-Taiba terrorist Junaid Ahmed Bhat was killed. He allegedly used his father's army knife, pre-planning the attack and researching poisoning methods.  Despite previous threats against his sister, neighbors described Arjun as quiet and disciplined, expressing shock at the horrific crime.  He showed no remorse during the crime scene reconstruction.

description: A woman tragically died during a crowded special premiere of "Pushpa 2" in Hyderabad, prompting the Telangana government to ban early morning screenings.  Revathi and her son were trampled amidst the chaos; she died from her injuries, while her son remains critically injured. Allu Arjun's team and the filmmakers have offered condolences and support.

description: Delhi-NCR schools reopen for in-person classes: Delhi schools are reopening with the considerable improvement in air quality. The Commission for Air Quality Management (CAQM), with Supreme Court approval, downgraded restrictions from Stage IV to Stage II of the Graded Response Action Plan (GRAP).  The improved AQI, now in the 'moderate' category, prompted the Directorate of Education to resume in-person classes for all schools.

description: Shubman Gill's return to the Indian Test side was short-lived as he fell to Scott Boland for the third time in as many innings in the second Test against Australia. Gill and KL Rahul built a promising partnership before a mini-collapse saw India lose three quick wickets, eventually being bowled out for 180.

description: Google CEO Sundar Pichai threw down the gauntlet to Microsoft CEO Satya Nadella.  Pichai proposed a direct comparison of their AI models. Pichai believes Google is well-positioned to lead in the age of AI.

description: Delhi Chief Minister Arvind Kejriwal accused the BJP of orchestrating the removal of thousands of voters from electoral rolls in key constituencies ahead of the Delhi Assembly elections. Kejriwal cited Shahdara, where the AAP narrowly won in the previous election, as an example, claiming 75% of 500 checked names on a BJP deletion application were still valid residents.

description: Virat Kohli's struggles against deliveries outside off-stump continued in the pink-ball Test, as he was dismissed for just 7 runs by Mitchell Starc. description: The Reserve Bank of India (RBI) raised its inflation forecast for fiscal year 2025 to 4.8% due to a surge in food prices. Retail inflation hit 6.2% in October. description: KL Rahul's promising start of 37 runs in the Adelaide Test against Australia ended in frustration as he was caught by Nathan McSweeney off Mitchell Starc's bowling. title: India’s first Hyperloop test track is ready! Railway minister shares an update

description: Six former Apple employees, led by Siu Kei Kwan, were charged with defrauding the company's gift-matching program. They also falsely claimed these donations on their tax returns, leading to charges of grand theft, conspiracy, perjury, and tax fraud.

description: Pushpa 2 is ruling the box office. The film earned over Rs 8.73 crore by 11 am on its second day.  Day 1 saw a massive Rs 175.1 crore net collection. description: Congress MP Priyanka Gandhi defended her brother, Rahul Gandhi, against BJP MP Sambit Patra's accusation of being a "traitor." title: Baahubali producer's WhatsApp account hacked: Shares how it happened

description: India faltered late in the first session of the second day-night Test against Australia in Adelaide. Mitchell Starc dismissed KL Rahul (37) and Virat Kohli (7) in quick succession, while Scott Boland trapped Shubman Gill (31) lbw. India slumped from 69/1 to 82/4 at Tea, losing three wickets for 12 runs in the space of 16 balls.
title: 3 wickets in 16 balls! India rattled by Rahul, Kohli, Gill blows

description: Opposition leaders, including Rahul Gandhi and Priyanka Gandhi Vadra, protested outside Parliament over the Adani issue.  Priyanka Gandhi praised her brother's commitment to the country.  Opposition members wore masks and t-shirts criticizing the Modi-Adani relationship.  They demanded a parliamentary committee and Modi's presence, leading to Lok Sabha adjournment.
title: Watch: Constitution in hand, Rahul, Priyanka protest over Adani issue

description: Yashasvi Jaiswal's vulnerability against left-arm pacers continued in the Adelaide pink-ball Test, falling to Mitchell Starc's first ball for a duck. This follows a similar dismissal in the first Test, despite his impressive 161 in the second innings. Jaiswal's struggles extend beyond Starc, with South Africa's Nandre Burger dismissing him thrice in recent series.
title: India vs Australia: How left is not right for Yashasvi Jaiswal

description: Jeff Bezos, Amazon's founder, is dedicating 95% of his time to the company's AI initiatives.  He's collaborating with Anthropic to build a supercomputer, aiming to compete with Google, Microsoft, and OpenAI.  Bezos remains executive chairman and actively supports CEO Andy Jassy, mirroring a trend of tech founders re-engaging with their companies amidst the AI boom.
title: Jeff Bezos is back at Amazon just 3 years after his retirement

description: Congress MP Abhishek Manu Singhvi denied having a "wad of currency" at his Rajya Sabha seat, claiming he carries only a single Rs 500 note. Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar revealed security staff found currency notes at Singhvi's seat after Thursday's session, prompting opposition protests and calls for an investigation.
title: 'I carry one Rs 500 note': Singhvi reacts to allegations of cash found at RS seat

description: Moflin, an AI pet, offers comfort and companionship. It interacts through movements and sounds.  Moflin learns and adapts to its owner.  It provides a personalized connection. The AI pet reacts to touch and voice. It has a five-hour battery life. Moflin is available in Japan and  a wider availability is planned.
title: How this cute AI pet is redefining companionship

description: Actress Amber Heard, 38, is expecting her second child, her representative confirmed to People magazine. The Aquaman star is already mom to three-year-old Oonagh Paige, born via surrogacy in 2021. While details about the pregnancy and how Heard plans to welcome her second child are scarce, the representative shared that Heard is "delighted.
title: Amber Heard expecting second child; actress 'delighted' to expand family

description: India chose to bat first after winning the toss against Australia in the second Test at Adelaide Oval. Australian players wore black armbands in memory of Phillip Hughes on the 10-year anniversary of his tragic passing and Ian Redpath, who recently died. Hughes' death led to significant safety improvements in cricket.
title: Why Aussies are wearing black armbands in pink-ball Test

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi led the nation in paying homage to Dr. B.R. Ambedkar on his 69th Mahaparinirvan Diwas at Parliament House.  Several dignitaries, including Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar and Congress President Mallikarjun Kharge, also paid their respects.  December 6th marks the anniversary of Dr. Ambedkar's death, the chief architect of India's Constitution and a champion of social justice.
title: PM Modi pays tribute to Dr BR Ambedkar on 69th Mahaparinirvan Diwas

description: India captain Rohit Sharma has shuffled the playing XI for the second Test against Australia, a day-night match in Adelaide. Rohit, Gill, and veteran spinner Ravichandran Ashwin return, replacing Padikkal, Jurel, and Sundar. Ashwin's impressive pink-ball record, including 18 wickets in five matches, and his reliable batting at number six influenced the decision.
title: Why Ashwin ahead of Washington makes sense for Adelaide Test

description: A key suspect in the targeted killing of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson has been identified through hostel CCTV footage. A flirtatious exchange with a female employee led to the unmasking. The suspect, seen talking on a phone before the shooting, purchased refreshments at a Starbucks afterward.
title: How 'flirting' unmasked CEO killer suspect: Story behind viral grinning pic

description: India's second Test against Australia at the Adelaide Oval began with a shaky start.  KL Rahul, replacing Rohit Sharma as opener, survived two scares in one over.  Scott Boland, returning to Test cricket, had Rahul caught behind off a no-ball and then dropped at first slip in the same over. India struggled at 19/1 after the initial overs.
title: Drama as KL Rahul survives off no-ball, Virat Kohli returns to pavilion

description: Islamist rebels seized Hama, advancing closer to Damascus in Syria's ongoing civil war.  The city holds historical significance due to the 1982 Hama Massacre, where Hafez al-Assad's forces killed thousands.  Russia monitors the situation, while Hezbollah pledges support to the Syrian government against the rebels.
title: With over 14 years of civil war, why is history haunting Syria

description: Zerodha CEO, Nithin Kamath, addressed the frequent issue of insurance claim rejections, emphasizing the need for policyholders to fully understand their coverage and exclusions.  He highlighted common rejection reasons like waiting periods, non-covered treatments, fraudulent claims, and blacklisted hospitals. Kamath advised seeking professional help if needed when dealing with claim denials.
title: Zerodha CEO answers biggest insurance question: Why claims are rejected & more

description: India's second Test against Australia at the Adelaide Oval started poorly as opener Yashasvi Jaiswal was dismissed for a golden duck by Mitchell Starc. Jaiswal was trapped leg-before-wicket in the first over, opting not to review the decision. This follows his contrasting performances in the first Test, where he scored a duck and then a match-winning 161.
title: Golden duck! Yashasvi Jaiswal dismissed off first ball in Adelaide

description: A mysterious illness, dubbed "Disease X," has struck the Democratic Republic of Congo, sickening hundreds and claiming at least 79 lives since late October.  Resembling the flu, the disease primarily affects young children, with symptoms including fever, cough, and breathing difficulties.  Health officials are working to identify the cause and contain the outbreak amidst heightened influenza activity.
title: Mystery ‘Disease X’ probed after killing 79 people in Congo

description: Billionaire Kenneth Griffin's record-breaking stegosaurus fossil, nicknamed Apex, will be displayed at the American Museum of Natural History for four years.  The loan allows public viewing and research access, including 3D scans for scientists. While paleontologists raise concerns about privately owned specimens, the museum emphasizes the fossil's scientific and public value.
title: World's priciest Dinosaur fossil arrives in New York with a staggering price tag

description: A 7.0 magnitude earthquake struck off the Northern California coast, triggering tsunami warnings but causing minimal damage.  The quake, centered near the Mendocino Triple Junction, shook homes and stores, sending items tumbling from shelves.  Widespread power outages occurred in Humboldt County, but schools resumed classes after evacuations. While the tremor was powerful, its remote location and horizontal fault movement mitigated the impact.
title: Viral videos show California’s 7.0 earthquake chaos

description: India opted to bat first in the second day-night Test against Australia at Adelaide Oval after Rohit Sharma won the toss.  Ravichandran Ashwin returned to the playing XI, replacing Washington Sundar. Sharma confirmed his return to the middle order, with Shubman Gill also coming in for Devdutt Padikkal. Australia's only change was Scott Boland replacing the injured Josh Hazlewood.
title: Ashwin returns as India make three changes for Pink-Ball Test

description: Astronauts Sunita Williams and Butch Wilmore have marked six months aboard the International Space Station after their initial week-long mission was extended due to issues with the Boeing Starliner capsule.  Despite the unexpected extended stay until February, the seasoned astronauts remain positive, contributing to station duties and scientific experiments while awaiting their SpaceX return flight.
title: 6 months in space, 2 to go: A look at Sunita Williams' journey so far

description: Maoists in Bijapur, Chhattisgarh, murdered two former sarpanchs, Suklu Farsa and Sukhram Avalam, for their alleged ties with the BJP.  The Maoists left leaflets on the bodies, warning other BJP workers to quit the party or face similar consequences.  Eleven BJP and three Congress functionaries have been killed in Bastar division since February 2023.  Police are investigating the murders.
title: Maoists target Chhattisgarh BJP, kill 2 ex-sarpanchs
Study ties C-section deliveries to income

description: A 19-year-old ITI diploma holder was tragically killed by a speeding train in Doddaballpur, Bengaluru, while attempting to cross the railway tracks to catch a screening of 'Pushpa-2'. The victim, Praveen Tamachalam, was en route to the theatre with two friends who fled the scene after witnessing the horrific accident.
title: 19-year-old boy rushing to watch 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' mowed down by train

description: Farmers in India are marching to Delhi to demand a legal guarantee for Minimum Support Price (MSP) for crops and other reforms.  Security is heightened at the Ambala-Delhi border, with prohibitory orders in place. This follows a previous attempt by farmers to march on Parliament earlier this week and an ongoing hunger strike at the Khanauri border.
title: 'Jatha' of 101 farmers to march towards Delhi today: All you need to know

description: UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson was shot dead in Manhattan.  "Deny, defend, depose" was written on the ammunition, echoing insurance industry tactics.  The incident has fueled public anger against insurance companies, sparking debate about healthcare affordability and industry practices.
title: Viral post that ‘decodes’ words on ammo used to gun down UnitedHealthcare CEO

description: India's Ministry of Electronics and IT (MeitY) is pressuring Meta Platforms to address WhatsApp scams following concerns raised by the telecom regulator.  MeitY is engaging with Meta, emphasizing user caution and complaint mechanisms.  The regulator seeks MeitY's intervention to curb scams originating on OTT platforms like WhatsApp, highlighting jurisdictional challenges and the need for stronger measures against spam and phishing.
title: Govt sends notice to WhatsApp after 'scam alarm' from telecom regulator TRAI

description: Allu Arjun's 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' faced online piracy after its theatrical release.  The film leaked on sites like Tamilrockers and Filmyzilla. This illegal distribution poses a threat to the film's earnings. Downloading pirated copies carries risks like malware and legal consequences.  Support 'Pushpa 2' by watching it legally in theaters.
title: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' leaked on Tamilrockers, & other sites; here's big danger warning

description: Bangladesh's interim government has waived the security clearance requirement for Pakistani visa applicants, signaling a potential thaw in bilateral relations.  This move follows the recent allowance of direct cargo shipments from Karachi to Chittagong, further suggesting improving ties between the two nations after a period of tension.
title: Pakistanis can now enter Bangladesh without security clearance

description: Allu Arjun's 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' continues its box office domination after a record-breaking opening day. Early estimates project a slight dip on Friday, yet the film remains on track for a phenomenal weekend. The Hindi version alone scored a remarkable Rs 65-67 crore net on day one, surpassing even Shah Rukh Khan's 'Jawan'.
title: 'Pushpa 2: The Rule' box office collection Day 2 early estimates

description: The Supreme Court eased anti-pollution measures in the National Capital Region (NCR), shifting from GRAP Stage 4 to GRAP-2 due to improved air quality. However, the court mandated immediate implementation of GRAP-3 if the Air Quality Index (AQI) exceeds 350 and GRAP-4 if it surpasses 400.
title: After 18 days of severe curbs, SC allows lifting of Grap-4

description: Devendra Fadnavis's swearing-in as Maharashtra CM was delayed due to Eknath Shinde's reluctance to be sworn in as Deputy CM. Shinde wanted assurances on portfolio allocation.  After persuasion, Shinde agreed, and Fadnavis informed the Governor. The oath-taking ceremony proceeded as planned, with both Fadnavis and Shinde taking their oaths.
title: Eknath Shinde kept all guessing till the last moment

description: Asian women, particularly in South Korea and Japan, are increasingly choosing to marry Western men.  Driven by deep-rooted patriarchal expectations in their own cultures, these women seek escape from traditional gender roles and unequal pay. They view Western marriages as offering greater gender equality and a chance for companionate partnerships.
title: Asian women vote against patriarchy with their feet

description: Bangladesh's interim government, led by Muhammad Yunus, has ordered the central bank to redesign banknotes, removing the image of Sheikh Mujibur Rahman. The new currency, featuring religious imagery and symbols of the July uprising, is expected within six months.
title: Bangladesh's new banknotes to exclude Mujibur's image

description: Maharashtra's new government swore in with unprecedented glamour at Mumbai's Azad Maidan.  A-list celebrities from Bollywood, business tycoons, and sports icons mingled with top political figures, including numerous Union ministers and chief ministers from various states. This high-profile event signaled the BJP's intent and set a new standard for political ceremonies in India.
title: Multistarrer premiere in Mumbai for Mahayuti-2
